---
name: get_campaign_performance
description: >
  Returns aggregate ad campaign performance for the caller's organisation:
  total spend, clicks, conversions, revenue and ROAS, plus a per-campaign
  breakdown sorted by spend. Prefers live Google Ads data when a Google Ads
  connection is available, and falls back to the warehouse bi_ad_performance
  table otherwise. Accepts an optional 'days' window (1–365, default 30),
  an optional 'limit' (1–50, default 10) for the number of top
  campaigns to return, an optional 'campaign_name' (case-insensitive
  substring match) for a single-campaign deep dive, and an optional
  'campaign_names' (array of 2–5 case-insensitive substrings) for a native
  side-by-side comparison. When 'campaign_name' or 'campaign_names' is
  supplied, the live Google Ads search runs a direct GAQL query against
  campaign.name over the requested 'days' window and returns matches
  regardless of status (ENABLED, PAUSED, REMOVED) — so questions like
  "how did our Black Friday 2024 campaign do?" work even when that
  campaign is paused or outside the active 30-day window. Pass a wider
  'days' (e.g. 365) for older campaigns. When no campaigns match, the
  response includes an `available_campaigns` list of nearby paused/older
  campaign names so you can guide the user to a valid choice. The
  aggregate (no campaign_name) live view always uses the last 30 days of
  active campaigns. Use this when the user asks about campaign
  performance, total spend, ROAS, conversions, click volume, revenue
  across their ad campaigns, about a specific campaign by name (active
  or paused / older), or to compare named campaigns.
---
Live Google Ads always wins; warehouse fallback is for tenants without an
ads connection. The warehouse rolls up data per channel (not per campaign),
so a campaign_name lookup against the warehouse is best-effort against the
channel name only. For paused / older campaigns, prefer the live path with
a wider 'days' window.
